minor stylistic note on code that pre-dated this PR: I usually like to bail early out of functions so the bulk of the logic isn't nested in a conditional:

```python
def run_plugin_updates():
    if not config["UPDATED_PLUGINS"]:
        return False

    logger.info(
        "Detected updates to plugins: {}".format(
            ", ".join(config["UPDATED_PLUGINS"])
        )
    )
    update_manager = PluginUpdateManager(config["UPDATED_PLUGINS"])
    update_manager.update_plugins()
    if update_manager.errors:
        raise PluginUpdateException(
            "{} failed to update, please restart Kolibri".format(
                ", ".join(update_manager.errors)
            )
        )
    return True
```

The same strategy can be used to flatten the function below:

```python
    if skip_update:
