@bryevdv Anything starting with `@` shouldn't be there, but there are different ways to deal with it:
  - For operations on `SearchIndexClient`, every request should set the `Accept` header to `application/json;odata.metadata=none`. That will ensure that `@odata.context` is not included in the response. In contrast, `SearchServiceClient` should set `Accept` to `application/json;odata.metadata=minimal` to avoid suppressing `@odata.type` annotations in the response (required for deserializing polymorphic model types), but that client doesn't have the same issues around representing documents (since documents are exclusively the domain of `SearchIndexClient`).
  - For any other annotation, they ought to be modeled in the Swagger as separate properties (true today for 2019-05-06), and the code generator should respect that by not putting them in `additionalProperties`.

